<title>NEW ZEALAND: Telecom buys shares from Bell, Ameritech.</title>
<headline>Telecom buys shares from Bell, Ameritech.</headline>
<dateline>WELLINGTON 1997-05-22</dateline>
<text>
<p>Telecom Corporation of New Zealand Ltd said on Thursday it had bought 616,230 shares on Wednesday at NZ$6.69 each, from Bell Atlantic Holdings and Ameritech Holdings.</p>
<p>The purchase is part of Telecom's on-going share buyback scheme.</p>
<p>The total number of issued shares in Telecom following these acquisitions is 1.826 billion, excluding 27.14 million shares held as treasury stock.</p>
<p>--Wellington Newsroom (64 4) 4734746</p>
